description:
Our client is an innovation and technology focus venture capital fund partnership with reputable universities in Hong Kong, the founder belongs a reputable local family office. They are currently looking for qualified individual to join the team assisting deal execution and fund operation. 



Responsibilities:
Perform fundamental, in-depth industry research analysis (TMT, Fin-tech);

Research involves spreadsheet modeling, interviewing management teams and extensive research with potential target companies;
Assist senior members to perform DD and execution on potential deals;
Assist in maintaining relations with existing LPs and pitching for new LPs;
Liaise with councils and fund admin to monitor the fund operation.

 Requirements:

Degree or above;
Work with passion, critical thinking and creativity;
CFA/CPA is a plus
Command of Bloomberg or Wind is a plus
High integrity, good communication skill

Responsibilities
Support the development of corporate sustainability strategies that reflect the environmental, social, and governance issues important to HUTCHMED;
Co-ordinate sustainability activities across Hong Kong, Shanghai, Suzhou and New Jersey operations;
Oversee implementation of sustainability goals and targ­ets across the R&D, manufacturing, China comm­ercial joint ventures and U.S. R&D / comm­ercial businesses;
Improve implementation methodologies, set annual milestones, and establish reporting mechanisms to inform employees and executive leadership on progress;
Support communication with investors and investment analysts regarding HUTCHMED’s sustainability position and progress (e.g. large mutual funds).
Communicate with ESG research firms and indices (e.g. MSCI, ISS Oekom, Sustainalytics);
Support the Board of Directors’ Sustainability Committee in strategic discussions and the exec­ution of sustain­ability focus areas;
Produce an annual corporate sustain­ability report, including data collection, measure­ment & analysis, stakeholder engagement and content devel­opment;
Liaise with the corporate public relations, investor rela­tions, commercial, marketing, Human Resources technical teams (mainly China & U.S.) to coordinate and drive sustain­ability positioning and actions;
Organise internal sustainability events and other enga­gements to promote and inspire staff.
Requirements

8 years minimum experience in a corporate environment in sustainability, compli­ance or finance, with some track record of delivering sustain­ability programmes;
Ability to influence change with internal business part­ners without direct reporting relationships;
Comfortable working with all levels of employees, from senior executives to front-line individual contributors;
Strong analytic, written and oral communication skills in English and preferably Mandarin Chinese;
Ability to manage and work collaboratively with cross-functional and cross-geographical working groups;
Ability to clearly articulate business value of sustain­ability investment.
Ability to multi-task, set priorities, and meet tight deadlines;
Entrepreneurial spirit to identify and act on new opportunities or improvements;
Educated to degree level in a sustainability, or business-related subject, or relevant work experience;
Interest or expertise in healthcare industry.


Salary and benefits will be commensurate with experience. Please send detailed resume with current and expected salary by clicking “APPLY NOW” in the below.
We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. The information provided will be treated in strict confidence and used only for consideration of application for relevant/similar post(s) within the CK Hutchison Group of Companies. Applicants not having heard from us within four weeks from the date of this advertisement may consider their application unsuccessful. All personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed after the recruitment exercise when no longer required.

HANG SENG INDEXES COMPANY LTD

Hang Seng Indexes Company Limited (‘Hang Seng Indexes Company’) manages and compiles the Hang Seng Family of Indexes, which cover stocks listed in Hong Kong and Mainland China. Our index series includes the Hang Seng Index, the Hang Seng China Enterprises Index and the Hang Seng TECH Index, as well as Stock Connect, Greater Bay Area and sector-related indexes. As at the end of 2019, assets under management in products passively tracking indexes in the Hang Seng Family of Indexes had reached a total of about US$38 billion.

Hang Seng Indexes Company is a wholly owned subsidiary of Hang Seng Bank. Our company is a team of professionals who strives for delivering quality, efficient and world-class index complier services to customers and financial institutions around the world.

We are currently seeking a high caliber professional to join our department as Business Transformation Manager.

Principal responsibilities

Provide project management and consultancy services on project/ system implementation, workflow design, and process re-engineering to various stakeholders in the Company;
Actively monitor the project scope and resources to meet the project schedule and budget;
Coordinate between users and internal IT team or external vendors to ensure an effective project implementation;
Proactively manage all the potential risks on projects and recommend mitigating measures if required;
Assist in collection of user requirements, conduct user acceptance tests, prepare training materials and conduct user training to support system/ project roll out


Requirements

University degree in Information System, Business Administration or a related discipline;
Minimum eight years of working experience, preferably with system project management or business analyst background in financial institutions;
Previous experience as a project manager in medium-to-large scale projects will be a plus;
Strong managerial, project management, communications, analytical, problem-solving, planning and organizing skills;
Ability to work independently, cope with pressure and meet tight deadlines;
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Knowledge of index industry and HK and China stock market is an advantage;
Experience in Agile project management is preferable;
PMP/ Lean Six Sigma certification is an advantage;
Familiar with HSBC Change Framework, Data Platform and Analytics would be an advantage;
Great sense of ownership and servicing mindset to ensure efficient and effective customer service processes
Candidates with less experience will be considered for the position of Assistant Business Transformation Manager.

If you would like to explore other opportunities at Hang Seng Hong Kong, please visit www.hangseng.com/careers/ for details.

The health and safety of our employees and candidates is very important to us. Due to the current situation related to the Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV), we’re leveraging our digital capabilities to ensure we can continue to recruit top talent at the HSBC Group.  As your application progresses, you may be asked to use one of our digital tools to help you through your recruitment journey.  If so, one of our Resourcing colleagues will explain how our video-interviewing technology will be used throughout the recruitment process and will be on hand to answer any questions you might have.

All information provided by applicants will be used only for recruitment purposes and will be used strictly in accordance with the Bank's personal data policies, a copy of which may be obtained by the applicant upon request. Unless otherwise instructed in writing by the applicant concerned, applicants may be considered for other suitable positions within the Bank and its related companies. The personal data of unsuccessful job applicants may be retained for a maximum of two years from the date when the job application is rejected and such data may be retained for a longer period if there is a subsisting reason that obliges the Bank to do so, after which the personal data will be destroyed.

Your role:

Responsible for lead generation and prepare tracking reports to support various marketing campaigns;
Develop Dashboards to facilitate efficient data analysis for product performance, customer profiles and campaign effectiveness;
Conduct quantitative analysis and data mining to support management decisions and provide data-driven recommendations;
Organize and prepare regular reports relating to business performance and service usage;
Conduct user acceptance test of in-house-developed applications.

To succeed in this role

University graduate in Computer Science, Information Technology, Data Science, Statistics or relevant discipline;
3 – 4 years’ relevant experience, preferably in data analysis, database programming or database management
Proficient in SAS, SQL, Python or other data mining tools;
Practical experience in data visualization tools (e.g. Qlik View/Sense, Power BI or Tableau);
Good analytical and problem solving skills, able to work under tight timeline;
Self-motivated and able to accomplish multiple tasks with minimal supervision;
Good interpersonal and communication skills and able to work with people at all levels;
Good command in both spoken and written English;
Candidate with less experience will be considered for the position of Senior Customer Data Analyst.

HKT is an equal opportunity employer and welcomes applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and will only be used for recruitment-related purposes. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with the employer's privacy statement (http://www.hkt.com/privacy-statement), a copy of which will be provided immediately upon request.

Duties: The appointee will be responsible for performing high-quality analyses, conducting research and overseeing the timely delivery of quality outcomes for internal and external projects, developing value propositions and presenting to relevant committees, sharing on best international practices related to examinations, assessments and research, giving expert advice to Secretariat staff and other parties, and helping the Division Head oversee the smooth running of the Division with the objective of enhancing organizational practices and processes within the human and financial resources given.

Requirements:

A doctoral degree in Education, Statistics, Measurement and Assessment or related disciplines;
At least 6 years of managerial experience, preferably in management of research work;
Abundant knowledge of research concepts and methods;
Substantial knowledge of statistical tools and assessment technology;
Familiarity with multidimensional item response theory and/or cognitive diagnostic modeling is preferred;
Excellent analytical skills and professional report writing skills;
Outstanding presentation and communication skills in Cantonese, English, and Putonghua;
Experience in working with primary and/or secondary schools in Hong Kong is an advantage;
Good interpersonal skills and teamwork spirit; and
Candidates with less working experience will also be considered.

Employment Terms:  The remuneration package will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Appointment will be on a fixed-term contract with contract-end-gratuity, MPF benefits, medical and dental care.  Future employment may be offered on renewable contracts subject to performance and staffing needs.

Date for Application Review: 28 January 2022

Applications would be considered until the post is filled.

Application forms can be obtained from the HKEAA office on 13/F., Southorn Centre, 130 Hennessy Road, Wan Chai, Hong Kong or downloaded from the HKEAA website (www.hkeaa.edu.hk/tc/Career/general.html).  Completed application forms should be returned to the Manager – Human Resources at the above address. Due to the secrecy nature of HKEAA's job duties, applicants invited for interview may be required to make a declaration of any conflict of interests. Applicants not notified within 10 weeks from the application review date should consider their applications unsuccessful.

The HKEAA is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided relating to employment will be kept confidential and used only for processing applications. For details, please refer to the Policy Statement on Equal Opportunities and the Personal Information Collection Statement on the HKEAA website (www.hkeaa.edu.hk).

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:

1. Work closely with Zhuhai headquarters to organize, direct, coordinate and control the business activities so as to ensure the realization of the business plan and guard against all kinds of risks;

2. Assist the senior Management to develop business strategies, business plans, organizational structure, risk management policies etc. for the company;

3. Coordinate with all departments to streamline and strengthen existing business operations and controlling procedures;

4. Generate regular reports/statistics to monitor the business operations performance, propose corrective & improvement actions, and develop the performance evaluation for internal departments;

5. Keep abreast of market information, government policies and business trends, give advices to the senior Management for the new business opportunities;

6. Preform any ad hoc duties assigned by the Company


REQUIREMENTS:

1. Degree in Economics, Finance, or Business Administration related disciplines;

2. Experienced in state-owned enterprise of China/ Chinese enterprise is a plus;

3. 3-5 years solid experiences in business management;

4. Be self-motivated and a good team player with excellent communication, interpersonal and influencing skills;

5. Mature, detailed-oriented, meticulous with strong time management and organizing skills;

6. Proficient in Cantonese, Putonghua and English, good Chinese writing skill;

7. Immediately available is highly preferred.

One of our clients is now looking for a high calibre candidate to fill the following position:


Degree holder;

1 year or above relevant experience;

Perform analysis on problems reported by users and give solutions;

Execute business application projects consistent with customer’s requirements;

Provide technological support and training to customers;

Working with large demanding customers and product team for enhancement discussions/solution planning;

Knowledge in programming is an advantage;

Experience in Network Infrastructure and Computer Hardware Support is an advantage;

Travel between Hong Kong, PRC & Macau may be required after Covid;

Proficiency in both spoken and written Cantonese, Mandarin & English.

Remarks:
Monthly Salary: HK$20-30K + Incentive;

5-day work;

Working location: Shatin;

Good fringe benefits e.g. medical, banking holiday, will be provided.

